propDescriptions.autoComplete: This prop helps users to fill forms faster, especially on mobile devices. The name can be confusing, as it's more like an autofill. You can learn more about it following the specification.
propDescriptions.autoFocus: If true, the input element is focused during the first mount.
propDescriptions.color: The color of the component. It supports both default and custom theme colors, which can be added as shown in the palette customization guide.
propDescriptions.componentsProps: The props used for each component slot.
propDescriptions.defaultValue: The default value. Use when the component is not controlled.
propDescriptions.disableFuture: If true disable values before the current date for date components, time for time components and both for date time components.
propDescriptions.disableIgnoringDatePartForTimeValidation: Do not ignore date part when validating min/max time.
propDescriptions.disablePast: If true disable values after the current date for date components, time for time components and both for date time components.
propDescriptions.error: If true, the label is displayed in an error state.
propDescriptions.focused: If true, the component is displayed in focused state.
propDescriptions.format: Format of the date when rendered in the input(s).
propDescriptions.fullWidth: If true, the input will take up the full width of its container.
propDescriptions.hiddenLabel: If true, the label is hidden. This is used to increase density for a FilledInput. Be sure to add aria-label to the input element.
propDescriptions.id: The id of the input element. Use this prop to make label and helperText accessible for screen readers.
propDescriptions.InputLabelProps: Props applied to the InputLabel element. Pointer events like onClick are enabled if and only if shrink is true.
propDescriptions.InputProps: Props applied to the Input element. It will be a FilledInput, OutlinedInput or Input component depending on the variant prop value.
propDescriptions.inputRef: Pass a ref to the input element.
propDescriptions.label: The label content.
propDescriptions.margin: If dense or normal, will adjust vertical spacing of this and contained components.
propDescriptions.maxRows: Maximum number of rows to display when multiline option is set to true.
propDescriptions.maxTime: Maximal selectable time. The date part of the object will be ignored unless props.disableIgnoringDatePartForTimeValidation === true.
propDescriptions.minRows: Minimum number of rows to display when multiline option is set to true.
propDescriptions.minTime: Minimal selectable time. The date part of the object will be ignored unless props.disableIgnoringDatePartForTimeValidation === true.
propDescriptions.multiline: If true, a textarea element is rendered instead of an input.
propDescriptions.name: Name attribute of the input element.
propDescriptions.onChange:
Callback fired when the value changes.

Signature:
function(value: TValue, The: FieldChangeHandlerContext<TError>) => void
value: The new value.
The: context containing the validation result of the current value.
propDescriptions.onError:
Callback fired when the error associated to the current value changes.

Signature:
function(error: TError, value: TValue) => void
error: The new error.
value: The value associated to the error.
propDescriptions.onSelectedSectionsChange:
Callback fired when the selected sections change.

Signature:
function(newValue: FieldSelectedSections) => void
newValue: The new selected sections.
propDescriptions.placeholder: The short hint displayed in the input before the user enters a value.
propDescriptions.readOnly: It prevents the user from changing the value of the field (not from interacting with the field).
propDescriptions.required: If true, the label is displayed as required and the input element is required.
propDescriptions.rows: Number of rows to display when multiline option is set to true.
propDescriptions.select: Render a Select element while passing the Input element to Select as input parameter. If this option is set you must pass the options of the select as children.
propDescriptions.selectedSections: The currently selected sections. This prop accept four formats: 1. If a number is provided, the section at this index will be selected. 2. If an object with a startIndex and endIndex properties are provided, the sections between those two indexes will be selected. 3. If a string of type MuiDateSectionName is provided, the first section with that name will be selected. 4. If null is provided, no section will be selected If not provided, the selected sections will be handled internally.
propDescriptions.shouldDisableTime:
Disable specific time.

Signature:
function(timeValue: number, view: TimeView) => boolean
timeValue: The value to check.
view: The clock type of the timeValue.
returns (boolean): If true the time will be disabled.
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.
propDescriptions.type: Type of the input element. It should be a valid HTML5 input type.
propDescriptions.value: The selected value. Used when the component is controlled.
